abstract: POUGHKEEPSIE, N.Y., Oct 10. -- Shortly after 6 o'clock this morning a heavy freight train of sixty cars left here going north on the Hudson River Railroad. abstract: WASHINGTON, Oct. 13. -- Commodore Ramsay, Acting Secretary of the Navy, received a telegram this morning from Lieut. Wadeworth, Inspector Life-Saving Service, dated Assateague, saying that the Despatch is broken up forward of the engines. The upper works are washed off. Little material was coming ashore. abstract: WASHINGTON, Oct. 30. -- A dead silence has settled down over the State Department as to the Chilean affair. It extends beyond and rests upon the Junta Legation. Senor Montt is silent, and even Julio Foster says not a word. In official circles the insinuation is allowed to ooze out that the situation is serious, and that both the President and Mr. Blaine are with difficulty suppressing their indignation at the insolence of Chile.
